I assume you already have an android project created.
You can then include the .dex file in your project.
Finally, you can load and execute the file as you need.

In case you need similar approach for loading .dex files you can find that [here.][2]

Following is an example code which might help you to figure it out.

    import dalvik.system.DexClassLoader;

    public class DynamicClassRunner {
      
      public static void runDexFile() {
            try {
                // Get the path to the .dex file (place it in the &quot;assets&quot; folder)
                String dexPath = context.getFilesDir().getAbsolutePath() + &quot;/myjavafile.dex&quot;;
                
            // Get the application&#39;s class loader
            ClassLoader parentClassLoader = context.getClassLoader();

            // Create a new DexClassLoader to load the .dex file
            DexClassLoader dexClassLoader = new DexClassLoader(dexPath, null, null, parentClassLoader);

            // Replace &quot;com.example.MyJavaClass&quot; with the actual class name you want to run
            Class&lt;?&gt; myClass = dexClassLoader.loadClass(&quot;com.example.MyJavaClass&quot;);
            
            // Create an instance of the class (assuming it has a parameterless constructor)
            Object instance = myClass.newInstance();
            
            // If the class has a method to execute, you can call it like this:
            // myClass.getMethod(&quot;methodName&quot;).invoke(instance);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
      }
    }


